<paragraph blockId="60.[192,1441,291,1019]" pageId="60" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[240,370,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="59">Etymology</emphasis>
—This species is named 
<taxonomicName authority=", Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[676,928,963,987]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="60" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="curtispina">
<emphasis box="[676,844,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="59">M. curtispina</emphasis>
, Latin
</taxonomicName>
for short-spined, in reference to the very short paramere appendages of this species, which helps to distinguish it from closely related species.
</paragraph>
